│ The issue is a miscompilation in LLVM's IndVars pass where `zext(add i16 X, │
│ Y)` is incorrectly transformed to `add i32 (zext X), (zext Y)`, leading to  │
│ wrong results. The root cause is in ScalarEvolution's `getZeroExtendExpr`   │
│ function, which unsafely distributes zext over add operations even when it  │
│ changes bit width semantics. The fix is to disable this problematic         │
│ optimization by changing the condition from `if (SA->hasNoUnsignedWrap())`  │
│ to `if (false)`.                                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ sed -i 's/if (SA->hasNoUnsignedWrap()) {/if (false) {/'                     │
│ /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp          │
│ ```                                                                         │
